## Initializing a Structure

To initialize a structure, you can use the following syntax:

```c
struct_name struct_variable = {field1_value, field2_value,...};
```

Here is an example of initializing a structure:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

typedef struct {
    char name[100];
    int status;
} person;

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    // initialize a new person with name "John" and status 1
	person p = {"John", 1};

    // print the person's name and status
	printf("Name: %s\n", p.name);
	printf("Status: %d\n", p.status);

    return 0;
}
```

The output of the program is:

```
Name: John
Status: 1
```

The `name` field is initialized with "John", and the `status` field is set to 1.

